    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM performance. This example retains the original 13B-REW rotary engine, featuring a meticulously maintained sequential twin-turbocharger setup that delivers linear boost across the powerband. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis exhibits zero structural fatigue, preserving the legendary 50/50 weight distribution and double-wishbone suspension geometry. Finished in its original factory paint with no oxidation, the exterior is matched by a cockpit free of bolster wear or dash shrinkage. Compression test results are optimal, ensuring this rotary remains as potent as the day it left Hiroshima. A rare, mechanically pristine survivor for the serious enthusiast.",
